I don't think image maps is the right tool for this, and in general HTML shouldn't be used for layout purposes.<br /><br />I think a better design is to use an SVG or PNG image and make text wrap at non-transparent parts of the image. Since such images can be either part of the content or just for decoration, it should probably work for both floated images and for background images.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Sun Jul 19, 2009 8:05 am</p><hr />
